---
---
<div class="term-pane-header">
  <div class="tui-panel-header"><span>GETTING STARTED</span></div>
</div>
<div class="term-pane" >
  <h2 class="section-header fg-green">// from zero to running agent //</h2>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ STEP 01 · INSTALL -->
  <div class="tui-step-header"><span><span class="step-num">01</span> · INSTALL</span></div>
  <pre class="code-block bash-block"><code class="copy-target">go install github.com/8op-org/gl1tch@latest</code></pre>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 24px;line-height:1.8">
    glitch lands in <code class="fg-cyan">$GOPATH/bin</code> &mdash; make sure it&rsquo;s on your <code class="fg-cyan">$PATH</code>.
  </p>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ STEP 02 · PLUGINS -->
  <div class="tui-step-header"><span><span class="step-num">02</span> · PLUGINS</span></div>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 12px;line-height:1.8">
    Plugins extend GL1TCH with CLI tool adapters. Place wrapper YAML files in
    <code class="fg-cyan">~/.config/glitch/wrappers/</code>.
  </p>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:12px;margin:0 0 4px"><span class="fg-yellow">ollama</span> <span class="fg-comment">— local models</span></p>
  <pre class="code-block yaml-block"><code class="copy-target"># ~/.config/glitch/wrappers/ollama.yaml
name: ollama
type: sidecar
command: ollama
args: ["run", "&#123;&#123;model&#125;&#125;", "&#123;&#123;prompt&#125;&#125;"]</code></pre>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:12px;margin:12px 0 4px"><span class="fg-yellow">claude</span> <span class="fg-comment">— cloud AI</span></p>
  <pre class="code-block yaml-block"><code class="copy-target"># ~/.config/glitch/wrappers/claude.yaml
name: claude
type: sidecar
command: claude
args: ["-p", "&#123;&#123;prompt&#125;&#125;", "--model", "&#123;&#123;model&#125;&#125;"]</code></pre>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:12px;margin:12px 0 4px"><span class="fg-yellow">gh</span> <span class="fg-comment">— GitHub CLI</span></p>
  <pre class="code-block yaml-block"><code class="copy-target"># ~/.config/glitch/wrappers/gh.yaml
name: gh
type: sidecar
command: gh
args: ["&#123;&#123;args&#125;&#125;"]</code></pre>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:12px;margin:12px 0 4px"><span class="fg-yellow">jq</span> <span class="fg-comment">— JSON processor</span></p>
  <pre class="code-block yaml-block"><code class="copy-target"># ~/.config/glitch/wrappers/jq.yaml
name: jq
type: sidecar
command: jq
args: ["&#123;&#123;filter&#125;&#125;"]</code></pre>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ STEP 03 · OLLAMA -->
  <div class="tui-step-header"><span><span class="step-num">03</span> · OLLAMA</span></div>

  <div class="tui-callout">
    <span class="tui-callout-title">OLLAMA SUPERCHARGER</span>
    <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:12px;margin:0;line-height:1.8">Run fully local AI — no API key, no cloud, no cost.<br>Ollama supercharges GL1TCH with private, fast, offline models.</p>
  </div>

  <pre class="code-block bash-block"><code class="copy-target">ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:latest
ollama pull llama3.2
ollama serve</code></pre>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 24px;line-height:1.8">
    <code class="fg-cyan">qwen2.5-coder</code> is excellent for code tasks.
    <code class="fg-cyan">llama3.2</code> is great for general reasoning and brain context pipelines.
  </p>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ STEP 04 · FIRST PIPELINE -->
  <div class="tui-step-header"><span><span class="step-num">04</span> · FIRST PIPELINE</span></div>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 12px;line-height:1.8">
    Launch GL1TCH and run the brain Ollama E2E pipeline &mdash; it tests the brain feedback loop using a local model.
  </p>
  <pre class="code-block bash-block"><code class="copy-target">glitch</code></pre>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:12px 0;line-height:1.8">
    In the Switchboard &rarr; <span class="fg-yellow">PIPELINES</span> panel, select
    <code class="fg-cyan">brain-ollama-e2e</code> and press
    <kbd class="fg-yellow">Enter</kbd> to launch. Or run directly:
  </p>
  <pre class="code-block bash-block"><code class="copy-target">glitch pipeline run brain-ollama-e2e</code></pre>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:12px 0;line-height:1.8">
    <strong class="fg-yellow">Step 1</strong> <span class="fg-comment">(write_brain)</span> asks qwen2.5 to summarize itself and saves the result as a brain note.
    <strong class="fg-yellow">Step 2</strong> <span class="fg-comment">(use_brain)</span> asks qwen2.5 to reference that note &mdash; verifying the brain context feedback system works.
  </p>
  <pre class="code-block" style="color:var(--comment);font-size:12px;line-height:1.7"><code>[brain-ollama-e2e] step-write: running...
[brain-ollama-e2e] step-write: done (brain note saved)
[brain-ollama-e2e] step-read:  running (brain context injected)...
[brain-ollama-e2e] step-read:  done
pipeline complete &#10003;</code></pre>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ STEP 05 · FIRST AGENT -->
  <div class="tui-step-header"><span><span class="step-num">05</span> · FIRST AGENT</span></div>
  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 12px;line-height:1.8">
    Launch an interactive agent session directly from the Switchboard.
  </p>

  <ol style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;margin:0 0 16px;padding-left:20px;line-height:2">
    <li>Press <kbd class="fg-yellow">Enter</kbd> on the <span class="fg-yellow">AGENT RUNNER</span> panel in the Switchboard</li>
    <li>Select your provider (e.g., <code class="fg-cyan">Ollama</code>)</li>
    <li>Tab to <span class="fg-yellow">MODEL</span> &rarr; select <code class="fg-cyan">llama3.2 (Ollama)</code> or any available model</li>
    <li>Tab to <span class="fg-yellow">PROMPT</span> &rarr; type your task</li>
    <li>Optionally: Tab to <code class="fg-cyan">[ ] use brain context</code> and press <kbd class="fg-yellow">Space</kbd> to enable brain injection</li>
    <li>Press <kbd class="fg-yellow">Ctrl+S</kbd> to submit</li>
  </ol>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ BOTTOM NAV -->
  <p style="color:var(--comment);font-size:11px;margin-top:24px">
    <span class="fg-yellow">&rarr;</span>
    Press <span class="fg-yellow">8</span> for Labs
    &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
    <span class="fg-yellow">9</span> for Docs (use_brain reference)
    &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
    <span class="fg-yellow">4</span> for Plugins
  </p>
</div>
